Eslövs lärov. 24, fil. kand. 26, teol. kand. 29, prästv. 29. Past:adj. i Brågarp o. Nevishög, v. pastor i Asmund-torp 30, v. stadskommin. i Raus 31, stadskommin. i Karlshamn sed. 32, las :pred. sed. 32. Ordf. i Karlshamns kyrkl. ungd:krets o. i Karlshamns sjöm :miss :fören., led. av Karlshamns ungd :råd.
translated: Axelsson, Erik Folke, town minister, Karlshamn, born on March 7, 1903 in Höör, Malmöhus County. Son of Axel Nilsson and Emilia Kristoffersson. Married to Carin Bengtsson on March 31. Had a son named Bengt born in 1936. He took his exams from Eslövs läroverk in 1924, completed his Bachelor of Arts degree in 1926, Bachelor of Theology degree in 1929, and was ordained as a priest in 1929. He served as assistant pastor in Brågarp and Nevishög, assistant pastor in Asmundtorp in 1930, town minister in Raus in 1931, and town minister in Karlshamn from 1932 as well as a chaplain at the hospital since 1932. He was also the chairman of the youth association in Karlshamn's church and the Karlshamn seamen's missionary society. Additionally, he was a member of the Karlshamn youth council.
